## Agent Pack

This repo uses a repository-coordinator + specialist-sub-agents pattern. All
agent behavior is defined in `.github/agents/`:

- `.github/agents/{{REPO_NAME}}.agent.md` — repository coordinator (main entry point)
- `.github/agents/context-discovery.agent.md` — builds a Context Bundle from the repo index
- `.github/agents/planning.agent.md` — produces structured change plans
- `.github/agents/architecture.agent.md` — flow analysis (explain / impact / review modes)
- `.github/agents/implementation.agent.md` — applies approved plans to code
- `.github/agents/testing.agent.md` — generates / validates tests
- `.github/agents/review.agent.md` — code-review verdict (APPROVE / REQUEST CHANGES)

Downstream agents consume the **Context Bundle** built by `context-discovery`
from these durable artifacts:

- `site/content/repo-index.md` — curated subsystem map
- `taxonomy.yaml` — identifier registry (typed)
- `docs-manifest.yaml` — doc page status index

To regenerate any of these, run the `Bootstrap agents` workflow from the
Actions tab.

